content:
Perform cleanup tasks to ensure that your migrated content functions as expected.

Set the OmniStudio Designers to Use the Standard Data Model
As part of migration to OmniStudio Standard, execute an Apex class to set the OmniStudio designers to use the standard data model instead of the custom data model.
Update OmniStudio Customizations
To ensure that custom functions work as expected after migration, update their syntax in the metadata file for each migrated Omnistudio Data Mapper and Integration Procedure.

In the standard object data model, Data Mapper names can contain only alphanumeric characters. However, if you reference a Data Mapper elsewhere, such as in Apex, and its name contains special characters, manually change the name.
Integration Procedure types and subtypes can also contain only alphanumeric characters. If referenced elsewhere or their name contains special characters, manually change the name of the type or subtype.

Update Remote Actions
To ensure that remote actions work as expected after migrating from OmniStudio for Vlocity to OmniStudio Standard, update any Apex classes used in remote actions with the correct syntax.
Deploy Migrated Objects to Your Production Environment
